\begin_layout Section
Neural Network and Further Plans
\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Neural Network
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The complexity of Neural Networks arises not from the specialisation of
 neurons, but from their topology and nature of interconnection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Understanding how the topology of neural network affect signal propogation
 seems to be a very interesting filed of study as it might give some insight
 into how the same kind of action potential can be used to propogate complex
 iformation from the brain.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Separator

\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Further Plan
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Looking forward to design a network of many neurons using LIF model.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Both numerical(time driven) and exact solutions(event driven) simulations
 can be done.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Looking forward to do the event driven simulation of the network in which
 each neuron in the network is updated when there is an incoming spike.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
synaptic connections can be defined in terms of connectivity matrices.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
for the starting, identical synaptic and membrane time constants will be
 assumed for all neurons in the network which later might be modified to
 give different or even variable time constants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Separator

\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Separator

\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Sketch for simulations
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
To start with, a predetermined topology will be assigned to a network consisting
 of N neurons.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Various tests for spiking are decided to avoid unnecessary calculations
 of the spike time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
spike times will be calculated using Netwton raphson method.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A table of spike times will be created and the neurons are allowed to fire
 accordingly and updating the list after each firing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
At the end of the simulation table of data of the spikes and their timing
 for different neurons will be recorded.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
These data can be used to study the effect of topology on the synaptic transmiss
ion.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
